First he put me in the underpants drawer,
then he pushed me underwater,

246
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,920
then he forced me to eat meatloaf.

247
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:50,280
This is a disaster.
- Meatloaf!

248
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:51,880
The Series is only half over.
- Are you listening?

249
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:56,080
What am I gonna tell the Babe? We need
to pack all the gear for Chicago today.

250
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,520
The bat's not here.

251
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:03,040
Son, if you know what happened
to the bat, you need to come clean now.

252
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:07,200
- But that's what I'm trying to tell you.
- Stanley, this is a real mess.

253
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:09,200
I... I know, Mr. Robinson.

254
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:11,520
As the General Manager
of the New York Yankees,

255
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:14,000
I have no other choice. You're fired.

256
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:17,640
- Fired?
- Mr. Robinson, please.

257
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:21,600
Stanley, someone has to be held
responsible. It was your shift.

258
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:28,080
If Babe's bat is found, then I'll
reconsider, but, until then, I'm sorry.

259
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:32,080
Stanley, what are we gonna do?
We're gonna be out on the streets.

260
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:35,680
- I'll get another job. I'll get two jobs.
- There are no jobs.

261
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:39,600
Yankee, you were alone in that
locker room. Now the bat's missing.

262
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:40,800
- Stanley...
- Emily,

263
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,800
there was no security guard on duty.

264
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:45,880
Yes, there was. Maybe he took the bat.

265
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:50,080
That's enough.
Son, what happened to the bat?

266
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:51,520
I don't know.

267
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,800
- Go to your room.
- Why don't you believe me?

268
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:56,040
Go to your room.

269
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:06,400
What was all that?
What's with the coppers?

270
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:09,480
- Someone stole Babe Ruth's bat.
- Good.

271
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:13,800
- Screwie, my dad got fired.
- Not good.

272
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:17,640
Why would someone steal
Babe's lucky bat?

273
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:19,920
The Yankees are gonna lose
the Series for sure.

274
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:23,040
Whoa, kid, you're watching
way too many newsreels.

275
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:25,480
That lucky bat stuff
is a bunch of malarkey.

276
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:28,200
How do you know?
You were only in for one pitch.

277
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:29,480
Ooh, that hurt.

278
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,400
That guard had to take the bat.

279
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:34,240
Why would a Yankees security guard
steal Babe Ruth's bat?

280
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:38,160
Now, if it were a Chicago Cubs
security guard, that I could believe.

281
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,960
Wait a minute.

282
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:48,000
Hey, hey, hey, I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

283
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:49,760
I still can't breathe.

284
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:54,040
Hey, I knew I'd seen that face before.

285
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:57,240
What are you babbling about?

286
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,680
The security guard was Lefty Maginnis,

287
00:19:59,840 --> 00:20:01,120
pitcher for the Chicago Cubs.

288
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:03,960
Lefty's the biggest cheater
who ever stepped on a mound.

289
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:06,840
Lefty stole the bat so Babe can't hit.

290
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:10,360
The Yankees will lose the Series.
I've got to tell Dad.

291
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:12,280
Yeah, and don't forget to mention
that you heard it

292
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:15,000
from your friendly neighborhood
talking baseball.

293
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:17,120
Kid, this is just a crazy theory

294
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:20,320
and even if it were true,
no one's gonna believe you.

295
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,640
You don't have any proof.

296
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:24,080
- Then I'll get some proof.
- How?

297
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:27,040
Most of the Cubs are heading for Chicago.
What're you gonna do?

298
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,920
Sneak out of the house,
go down to Penn Station,

299
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:31,880
and search every single passenger?

300
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:34,000
- Right.
- Oh, no.

301
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,720
If we go to Penn Station,
we may catch him there.

302
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,560
I got to learn to keep my mouth shut.

303
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,080
Whoa! Oh!

304
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:42,560
This can't work. You're just a kid

305
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:45,320
and this is the real world,
not some fantasy land

306
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:48,160
- filled with gumdrop fairies and...
- You're coming with me.

307
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:52,360
Yeah, I think maybe not,
but thanks for the invite.

308
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:58,960
Screwie, I have to do this for my dad.

309
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:02,200
All right, don't look at me...
Don't look at me like that.

310
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:06,160
Stop it, stop...
Okay, fine, let's make a deal.

311
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:09,280
I'll help you to find the bat
if you take me back to the sandlot,

312
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:13,080
- and leave me to rot in peace. Deal?
- Deal.

313
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:15,400
Hmm.

314
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:22,960
Oh, whoa!

315
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:25,000
What are we doing?
What are we doing?

316
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,160
Uh-oh.
What do you mean by "uh-oh"?

317
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,000
Uh-oh! Uh-oh!

318
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:36,960
- Okay, we're fine.
- I'm okay.

319
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:38,240
Not fine!

320
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:42,160
My head! My butt! My head! My butt!

321
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:50,640
Oh!

322
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:54,000
- So far, so good.
- Are you okay?

323
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:56,760
- You were screaming pretty loud.
- I wasn't screaming.

324
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:59,120
I was laughing.

325
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:01,840
Ha! See? Ha, ha, ha! Ha! Ha! Ha!
Laughing.

326
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,600
There's a million people here.
How we gonna find Lefty?

327
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,800
Just keep looking, all right?

328
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:20,200
Flyer service to Niagara.
Track 18.

329
00:22:25,160 --> 00:22:26,080
We gotta hurry.

330
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,600
Why don't we come back in 10 years?
When you're taller.

331
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:32,880
Make way, there, folks.
Coming through, coming through.

332
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:37,360
See anything yet?

333
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:41,680
I see a sock, a candy wrapper,
a Life Saver covered in lint.

334
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:46,400
- Hmm. Pineapple.
- Screwie. This is no time to fool around.

335
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:48,080
Now do you see anything?

336
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,760
I see thousands of people
going about their business,

337
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:52,200
none of which is ours.

338
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:55,960
There's only one train to Chicago,
so Lefty will have to be on it.

339
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,560
- We're gonna stake it out.
- "Stake it out"?

340
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:00,720
What, what, what,
now you're with the FBI?

341
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:03,280
All aboard
for the County Peabody Express:

342
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,920
Better off rotting up
in that sandlot.

343
00:23:06,040 --> 00:23:08,600
I got to get stuck
with J. Edgar Hoover Junior, here.

344
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:13,000
How are we gonna cover the whole train?
There's like 50 cars and 100 passengers,

345
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:15,120
and... Holy Mackerel!

346
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:20,800
Bingo. That's got to be Babe's bat.

347
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:34,880
Okay, we found him. I'll give you that.
But anything could be in that case.

348
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,880
A trombone, a wooden leg, a pogo
stick.

349
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:41,360
Well, there he goes,
so I guess we'll never know. Too bad.

350
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:46,520
- Come on, boys.
- All aboard!

351
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,560
Hey, wait, wait.
Where are you taking me?

352
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:55,240
Take a head count
when you get inside, okay?

353
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,480
- I think that's him.
- Let's call the cops.

354
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:13,800
I'm not sure. Take a closer look.

355
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:16,040
- Wow!
- Is it him?

356
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:18,600
There's a horse jumping off a diving
board.

357
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:21,040
Wait, I think that's Eleanor
Roosevelt.

358
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,520
Screwie, is it Lefty or not?

359
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:30,440
Take a quick look as you roll yourself
back.

360
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,880
Roll myself back from...
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

361
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:38,000
Ow, what a headache! Nope. No.

362
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:42,800
Hello.

363
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,280
No.

364
00:24:53,760 --> 00:24:54,920
Did you see him?

365
00:24:56,200 --> 00:25:00,280
Third row, aisle seat.
Where are you going?

366
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,720
Good. You got it,
now take me back to the sandlot.

367
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:20,520
Oh, no!

368
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:24,520
Huh?

369
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,560
Uh-oh.

370
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:38,800
Oh, rats!

371
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,840
Oh, no!

372
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:56,120
Good. That thing's brought us
nothing but trouble.

373
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:57,440
Hey, you!

374
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,920
Stop right there.

375
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:04,600
I'm a ball.

376
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:08,400
I'm probably gonna survive this,
but you, you're a squishy little kid.

377
00:26:08,520 --> 00:26:09,560
Whoa.

378
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:11,440
Screwie.

379
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:16,000
Yankee, help me!

380
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,840
Give me back my box, kid.

381
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:31,480
Huh?

382
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,080
Oh!

383
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:51,800
Huh?

384
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:58,760
Oh, yeah, the kid's still got the
moves.

385
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:00,320
Sir, I need to see your ticket!

386
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,680
Whoa!

387
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,400
Whoa!

388
00:27:31,040 --> 00:27:32,840
Whoa!

389
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:34,760
Whoa!

390
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:37,280
Kid, you're gonna get such a time-out.

391
00:27:46,480 --> 00:27:48,440
The fun's over, you little punk.

392
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,840
Screwie, hang on!

393
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:04,440
Gotcha!

394
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:05,520
Hey, you...

395
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,600
Hit him! Use your elbow.

396
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:10,400
Kicking is good.

397
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:17,040
Oh, that can't feel good.

398
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:19,320
Doesn't really hurt so bad.

399
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,680
Wait. Yes, it does hurt.

400
00:28:21,840 --> 00:28:22,960
Here it comes. Oh, yeah.

401
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:26,640
Oh!

402
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:42,080
But I need to get to New York.

403
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:45,720
New York? That way.
You can buy yourself a ticket inside.

404
00:28:54,840 --> 00:28:55,800
Oh, great.

405
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:59,000
No tickets, no train, no sandlot.

406
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:02,440
What could be worse?

407
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:05,880
Well, at least I got the bat.

408
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:21,720
- Oh, here she goes again.
- Help me, somebody. Help me.

409
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:25,160
I'm not supposed to be here.
Help me!

410
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:27,160
Whoa, sister, relax.

411
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:29,320
You're a hunk of wood,
not the Hope Diamond.

412
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,720
Do you know who I am?

413
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:34,120
I am Darlin', honey. I'm the Babe's
bat.

414
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:38,480
Born of a 1000-year-old tree
on the side of Mount Olympus.

415
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:39,440
Struck by lightning,

416
00:29:39,600 --> 00:29:43,280
and carved by monks using
the horn of a unicorn.

417
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:45,200
Since when do monks make baseball
bats?

418
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:48,440
- Are you calling me a liar?
- No, of course not.

419
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:51,200
In fact, I was made
from the hide of Seabiscuit,

420
00:29:51,320 --> 00:29:53,920
and stitched together by Betsy Ross!

421
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:55,880
Screwie was in the Major Leagues, too.

422
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:58,640
He'd have been a home run ball,
if he hadn't fouled out.

423
00:29:58,760 --> 00:29:59,680
- Oh.
- Kid, don't.

424
00:29:59,800 --> 00:30:03,280
A foul ball? Really?
Well, isn't that impressive.

425
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:06,280
I've hit thousands of guys
that were better than you.

426
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:08,240
You know, you bats are all prima
donnas.

427
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:10,480
You only come out
three or four times a game,

428
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:12,120
carried to the plate and back.

429
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:16,080
"Oh, don't let me lay in this dirt.
Where's my batboy?"

430
00:30:16,200 --> 00:30:17,680
Well, here's what you know.

431
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:22,280
I don't need anybody to carry me around.
I can handle myself. Put me down.

432
00:30:23,520 --> 00:30:24,640
- Put me down!
- Whoa!

433
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,440
Okay.

434
00:30:28,600 --> 00:30:30,440
So long, farm team.

435
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:37,920
Excuse me.

436
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,080
Two.

437
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,520
You know something?

438
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:51,240
If you think
I'm rolling all the way to Chicago,

439
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:54,560
you've got another thing coming.
You may pick me up.

440
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,320
Lf, in fact, you're rescuing me,

441
00:30:57,440 --> 00:31:02,000
then I assume that you are returning me
to my rightful owner, Mr. Babe Ruth,

442
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:05,760
who, as I'm sure you're aware,
is currently in Chicago

443
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:07,760
playing in the World Series.

444
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:11,000
You have heard of the World Series,
haven't you, ball?

445
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:14,360
Oh, yeah,
I've heard of the World Series.

446
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:16,480
But we ain't going to Chicago,
we're going to New York.

447
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:18,600
New York? Why?

448
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:21,120
I just told you Babe is in Chicago.

449
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:23,960
When Lefty stole you, my dad got
fired.

450
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:26,960
If I take you to New York,
then he'll get his job back.

451
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:28,880
Oh, no, no, no.
You gotta take me to Babe.

452
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:32,600
Hey, table leg,
don't put any crazy ideas into his head.

453
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:35,400
We are not going to Chicago.
We are going to New York.

454
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:37,400
That's it. The baseball has spoken.

455
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:40,360
- But...
- I said, "The baseball has spoken. "

456
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:43,080
Fine, that's all right with me.

457
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:46,480
I just happen to know that
Mr. Babe Ruth is a generous man,

458
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:49,040
and I'm sure he could get
your daddy's job back.

459
00:31:49,160 --> 00:31:50,880
Maybe even with a big raise.

460
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:54,400
But y'all want to go to New York,
we'll go to New York.

461
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:56,800
Only you can make that decision.

462
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:03,000
Oh, Stanley, where could he be?

463
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:07,040
This is all my fault.

464
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:09,760
I was too hard on him.

465
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:11,480
How will we ever find him?

466
00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:15,200
I think it's time to call the police.

467
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:21,640
Ouch! Ouch!

468
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:38,920
Is that our train?

469
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:42,040
I don't think so.

470
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:43,960
Oh.

471
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:47,520
I know that smell.

472
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,960
Kid, kid, wake up.

473
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:53,160
Wake up.

474
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,160
- Hey, what do you...
- Quiet.

475
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:56,480
Lefty's here.

476
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:58,960
Oh, no.

477
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:03,880
Get it back some...

478
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,960
Oh, he's gonna be sorry.

479
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:11,480
I'll have a non-fat mochaccino,
please.

480
00:33:12,600 --> 00:33:14,800
Quiet, tentpole. It's the bad guy.

481
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:18,120
...use his head for batting practice.

482
00:33:18,320 --> 00:33:20,840
Whack, whack, whack, whack, whack.

483
00:33:21,040 --> 00:33:22,080
Babe Ruth, stop hitting yourself.

484
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,560
Seriously, why are you
hitting yourself, Babe?

485
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,880
- What?
- Hello, Mr. Cross, it's Lefty Maginnis.

486
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:30,360
Ah! Lefty.

487
00:33:30,480 --> 00:33:32,560
I've been expecting your call
for several hours.

488
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:35,440
- From now on, we have to talk in code.
- What?

489
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:37,680
Are you on the way to Cairo?

490
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:41,480
- I thought you wanted me in Chicago.
