and with only two outs to go,
they probably are:

973
01:02:49,680 --> 01:02:53,480
Well, I believe that's gonna do it
for your Yankees, Yankee.

974
01:02:57,960 --> 01:03:01,960
Oh... I suppose
this bat's not much of a threat now.

975
01:03:02,160 --> 01:03:04,840
I hope you get splinters everywhere.

976
01:03:04,960 --> 01:03:06,960
Of course there's always next year.

977
01:03:07,080 --> 01:03:08,680
Maybe I'll take her
to my cabin on the lake.

978
01:03:08,840 --> 01:03:12,000
There're some beavers there
that'd love to make her acquaintance.

979
01:03:12,160 --> 01:03:13,480
Give it a little nibble.

980
01:03:16,360 --> 01:03:20,160
I suppose I should be heading down to the
field to accept my World Series trophy.

981
01:03:20,280 --> 01:03:22,200
You just stay put, little Yankee.

982
01:03:22,320 --> 01:03:25,040
I'm sure your parents have given up
looking for you by now.

983
01:03:25,160 --> 01:03:27,800
The orphanage should be here
any minute to pick you up.

984
01:03:27,920 --> 01:03:29,000
Just walk in saying,

985
01:03:29,120 --> 01:03:32,480
"I'm the boy who lost Babe Ruth's bat
and cost him the World Series.

986
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:34,360
"How're you folks doing?"

987
01:03:38,400 --> 01:03:39,840
Sleep on that, Yankee.

988
01:03:45,280 --> 01:03:47,120
So what's the plan, Yank?

989
01:03:47,280 --> 01:03:49,960
- There is no plan, Screwie.
- You mean we're winging it?

990
01:03:50,080 --> 01:03:52,440
- Great. What do we do first?
- Nothing.

991
01:03:52,720 --> 01:03:56,400
There is nothing we can do.
Don't you get it? It's over.

992
01:03:56,520 --> 01:03:58,520
Babe struck out. We failed.

993
01:03:58,720 --> 01:04:01,560
You were right, Screwie. I'm just a
kid.

994
01:04:02,760 --> 01:04:04,880
I should have just quit.

995
01:04:05,240 --> 01:04:07,880
That's it? You're laying down your
bat?

996
01:04:08,000 --> 01:04:10,080
You know, when I landed in that
sandlot,

997
01:04:10,240 --> 01:04:13,760
I thought, "That's it.
There's nothing left to do but rot. "

998
01:04:13,920 --> 01:04:15,520
But then you came along.

999
01:04:15,680 --> 01:04:17,760
And there was all this...
This jumping on trains,

1000
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:21,360
and the thing with the apples
and playing ball with the Tigers.

1001
01:04:22,240 --> 01:04:24,040
You made a believer out of me.

1002
01:04:24,440 --> 01:04:27,200
I wasn't right, kid. Not at all.

1003
01:04:27,520 --> 01:04:30,840
So what, the Yankees lose a game?
Is that why you did this?

1004
01:04:30,960 --> 01:04:33,360
So Babe can set his millionth record?

1005
01:04:33,480 --> 01:04:38,000
Did Babe teach you how to throw?
Is Babe gonna pay your family's rent?

1006
01:04:38,480 --> 01:04:41,200
Why did you do this, Yankee? Why?

1007
01:04:42,760 --> 01:04:46,680
- To help my dad.
- Then the game's not over, Yankee.

1008
01:04:47,160 --> 01:04:49,520
Are you gonna keep swingin'?

1009
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:57,040
I thought baseball
was a field of broken dreams.

1010
01:04:57,160 --> 01:05:01,680
I'm not talking about baseball.
I'm talking about family.

1011
01:05:07,720 --> 01:05:10,720
- Darlin', we gotta...
- I heard everything he said.

1012
01:05:10,840 --> 01:05:14,840
Yankee, I would be honored to help
save your Daddy's job.

1013
01:05:15,720 --> 01:05:18,480
And here I thought you were
a hard-hearted old crank.

1014
01:05:18,600 --> 01:05:20,440
- All right...
- And now I come to find out

1015
01:05:20,560 --> 01:05:23,960
that under that tough leather shell
is just a gooey caramel center.

1016
01:05:24,080 --> 01:05:26,680
- Enough already.
- Fine.

1017
01:05:26,800 --> 01:05:30,040
Unless, of course,
you've got something else you wanna say.

1018
01:05:30,160 --> 01:05:32,000
You did good, baseball.

1019
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:35,040
Thanks, bat.

1020
01:05:35,160 --> 01:05:38,960
- So how're we getting out of here?
- The window.

1021
01:05:41,080 --> 01:05:45,640
- It doesn't open.
- Don't you get it? Baseball. Window.

1022
01:05:45,920 --> 01:05:47,640
Smasharoonie.

1023
01:05:50,240 --> 01:05:51,840
Screwie, are you sure?

1024
01:05:52,000 --> 01:05:54,400
Look at me.
I'm covered in stitches already.

1025
01:05:54,520 --> 01:05:57,480
Now, let's smash some glass!

1026
01:06:03,480 --> 01:06:06,040
Okay, I think
we're softening up the glass a little.

1027
01:06:06,160 --> 01:06:07,160
Try again.

1028
01:06:12,840 --> 01:06:13,760
Play ball!

1029
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:20,040
Screwie, where are you?

1030
01:06:23,440 --> 01:06:26,400
Don't worry about me. Get to the Babe.
I'll be all right.

1031
01:06:26,560 --> 01:06:28,040
Hey, a foul ball.

1032
01:06:28,280 --> 01:06:30,040
I just can't shake that, can I?

1033
01:06:30,160 --> 01:06:32,640
Whoa!
Hey, watch it, watch it! Hey!

1034
01:06:33,920 --> 01:06:34,920
Whoa!

1035
01:06:54,440 --> 01:06:58,120
You see, baseball is about teamwork,
a certain level of dignity...

1036
01:06:58,240 --> 01:06:59,160
What the?

1037
01:06:59,320 --> 01:07:00,720
Hey, kid!
Stop that kid.

1038
01:07:00,840 --> 01:07:01,760
Don't go down there.

1039
01:07:01,920 --> 01:07:03,440
Lou, that kid, I... I know that kid.

1040
01:07:03,560 --> 01:07:05,560
You remember that kid. That's the...
That, that... It's that kid.

1041
