- Tell him, Babe. You tell him.
- What?

1064
01:08:10,720 --> 01:08:12,680
That's the most absurd thing
I've ever heard!

1065
01:08:12,800 --> 01:08:14,600
Isn't that a penalty? Shouldn't they
forfeit?

1066
01:08:15,600 --> 01:08:17,880
Yankees, you got two minutes
to get your batter in the box

1067
01:08:17,960 --> 01:08:19,040
or you'll forfeit the game.

1068
01:08:19,160 --> 01:08:22,160
All right, right.
Hold your... Hold your horses.

1069
01:08:22,560 --> 01:08:25,040
It's not okay. We're in bad shape.
- Yankee. Yankee.

1070
01:08:25,160 --> 01:08:27,160
Do you notice where you're standing, boy?

1071
01:08:28,160 --> 01:08:31,160
Home plate in the middle
of the World Series.

1072
01:08:31,480 --> 01:08:33,560
Now how does that feel, slugger?

1073
01:08:34,240 --> 01:08:35,920
You're looking good, Yankee.

1074
01:08:36,600 --> 01:08:38,920
- Don't you think so, Babe? Babe? Babe!
- Darlin'.

1075
01:08:39,040 --> 01:08:40,600
- Big man, look over here!
- Darlin'.

1076
01:08:40,720 --> 01:08:43,240
- What are you doing?
- I'm calling to Babe.

1077
01:08:43,440 --> 01:08:46,880
Yeah, look at this team.
We look like we're already beat.

1078
01:08:47,040 --> 01:08:50,040
Who can we put at the plate
that will set this place on its ear?

1079
01:08:50,160 --> 01:08:52,760
Keep this team from
throwing in the towel.

1080
01:08:52,880 --> 01:08:54,560
Look at the boy
standing on home plate.

1081
01:08:54,680 --> 01:08:56,760
Ain't he something? Listen.

1082
01:08:57,120 --> 01:08:59,680
Hey! You hear me talking to you?

1083
01:08:59,800 --> 01:09:02,280
- Huh?
- Why don't you put him in the game?

1084
01:09:02,720 --> 01:09:04,640
Babe, look at us.

1085
01:09:06,400 --> 01:09:08,840
I know who's gonna bat. Him.

1086
01:09:09,040 --> 01:09:12,360
Babe, forget it. This isn't Little League.
It's the World Series.

1087
01:09:12,480 --> 01:09:13,800
He's just a kid.

1088
01:09:13,880 --> 01:09:17,000
This kid brought Darlin' from New York
to Chicago all by himself.

1089
01:09:17,120 --> 01:09:19,360
If he can do that, he can do anything.

1090
01:09:19,920 --> 01:09:23,600
Come on, guys. This is baseball.
Anything can happen.

1091
01:09:23,720 --> 01:09:25,120
What do you say?

1092
01:09:25,360 --> 01:09:26,520
Hmm.

1093
01:09:26,920 --> 01:09:29,960
All right, Yankees. Time's up.
Who's your hitter?

1094
01:09:30,080 --> 01:09:32,280
- Him. There's our hitter.
- Huh?

1095
01:09:32,440 --> 01:09:34,040
- What?
Play ball!

1096
01:09:34,200 --> 01:09:36,160
I... I don't know about
this.

1097
01:09:36,320 --> 01:09:40,080
You are about to bat in the World
Series!

1098
01:09:42,880 --> 01:09:45,800
I guess you guys really are desperate.

1099
01:09:51,680 --> 01:09:54,840
I know, I have no strike zone,
so don't swing.

1100
01:09:54,960 --> 01:09:58,720
Of course you swing.
Here, you can use my Darlin'.

1101
01:09:58,840 --> 01:10:01,320
But, Babe,
nobody's ever used Darlin' but you.

1102
01:10:01,440 --> 01:10:02,440
Yeah, well...

1103
01:10:03,680 --> 01:10:07,560
I don't want her to hear this,
but it's not really the bat,

1104
01:10:07,760 --> 01:10:09,320
it's the batter.

1105
01:10:10,480 --> 01:10:11,880
Now go get them, kid.

1106
01:10:12,920 --> 01:10:14,440
So what's happening? What did I miss?

1107
01:10:14,560 --> 01:10:17,000
- Yankee's gonna pinch hit.
- What?

1108
01:10:17,800 --> 01:10:20,840
I mean, what a great idea! Wow!

1109
01:10:20,960 --> 01:10:23,920
Who came up with that one?
Because that's a beauty, boy.

1110
01:10:24,040 --> 01:10:26,680
- Screwie!
- You can do it, Yankee,

1111
01:10:26,800 --> 01:10:29,080
and I'll be right here the whole time
to talk you through it.

1112
01:10:29,200 --> 01:10:30,360
Batter up!

1113
01:10:30,480 --> 01:10:33,600
Whoa! Scratch that.
I'll be right here.

1114
01:10:36,200 --> 01:10:39,080
I thought it was supposed to be Babe,
not a baby.

1115
01:10:39,240 --> 01:10:41,320
Well, sports fans,
the Yankees have put

1116
01:10:41,480 --> 01:10:43,680
a 10-year-old boy in as the pinch
hitter:

1117
01:10:43,840 --> 01:10:45,520
- A boy? What, are they kidding?
- Oh, I'm being given a name

1118
01:10:45,640 --> 01:10:46,920
for the young rookie:

1119
01:10:47,040 --> 01:10:49,880
- It's Yankee Irving:
- Yankee Irving?

1120
01:10:50,000 --> 01:10:54,440
Now batting for the New York Yankees,
number one, Yankee Irving:

1121
01:10:54,560 --> 01:10:56,960
- That's my boy!
- Yankee?

1122
01:10:57,080 --> 01:10:59,680
They're putting him in the game.
Yankee. Yankee.

1123
01:11:03,360 --> 01:11:06,800
Okay, Lefty, all you have to do
is strike the kid out.

1124
01:11:06,920 --> 01:11:08,080
Just finish it!

1125
01:11:08,200 --> 01:11:12,360
Okay, kid, you're about to lose
a whole lot of baby teeth.

1126
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:18,080
Settle in, Yank. You can do this!

1127
01:11:21,760 --> 01:11:24,000
Don't just stand there, you gotta
swing.

1128
01:11:24,120 --> 01:11:26,000
Strike one!

1129
01:11:26,120 --> 01:11:28,760
Okay, now you know
he's throwing strikes. Be ready.

1130
01:11:29,480 --> 01:11:30,600
He can do it.

1131
01:11:37,560 --> 01:11:40,280
Watch me, now, watch me!
Curveball! Curveball! Swing!

1132
01:11:40,880 --> 01:11:42,720
- Strike two!
- Darn!

1133
01:11:43,440 --> 01:11:46,080
Come on now, sugar.
I cannot swing myself.

1134
01:11:46,200 --> 01:11:47,200
Yank!
Yankee.

1135
01:11:47,360 --> 01:11:49,200
Yankee, we're here!
We're here!

1136
01:11:49,320 --> 01:11:50,600
- Yank!
- Yank, we're here!

1137
01:11:50,760 --> 01:11:52,400
Mom? Dad?

1138
01:11:52,480 --> 01:11:54,640
- Just swing!
- Just swing!

1139
01:12:03,880 --> 01:12:07,200
You get your feet set right,
you can hit anything you can reach:

1140
01:12:07,320 --> 01:12:09,720
MARTl: Keep your eye on the ball:

1141
01:12:10,000 --> 01:12:14,280
If Babe can do it, so can you:

1142
01:12:15,480 --> 01:12:18,680
- Oh, my.
- Time for the booger ball.

1143
01:12:28,320 --> 01:12:31,720
I can't believe you just blew
your nose on me.

1144
01:12:34,680 --> 01:12:36,200
Come on, Yankee.

1145
01:12:40,600 --> 01:12:42,640
Take your time. Focus!

1146
01:12:50,480 --> 01:12:51,400
Uh-oh.

1147
01:12:52,920 --> 01:12:56,680
I'm going! I'm going! I'm not going.

1148
01:12:58,960 --> 01:13:00,080
Run!

1149
01:13:01,480 --> 01:13:03,320
And he hit it!
The kid hit the ball!

1150
01:13:03,440 --> 01:13:04,720
Go, go, go, go, go.

1151
01:13:04,840 --> 01:13:07,160
It's a short blooper
and Irving is sprinting to first base!

1152
01:13:07,280 --> 01:13:09,600
I said I got it.

1153
01:13:10,160 --> 01:13:13,720
It sails right past Taylor,
the first baseman:

1154
01:13:14,000 --> 01:13:15,920
Go for second! Go for second!

1155
01:13:16,040 --> 01:13:18,880
Irving rounds first base
as Taylor and Cuyler chase it down:

1156
01:13:19,800 --> 01:13:21,280
Slide, Yankee!

1157
01:13:21,400 --> 01:13:23,560
Irving is rounding second
and is barreling towards third,

1158
01:13:23,680 --> 01:13:25,600
but I don't think he's gonna make it,
folks:

1159
01:13:25,760 --> 01:13:28,240
Go, Yankee, go!
- Come on, Yankee! Go!

1160
01:13:28,360 --> 01:13:30,040
Move it! Move it!

1161
01:13:30,840 --> 01:13:35,120
Lefty Maginnis is covering::: Holy
cow!

1162
01:13:35,240 --> 01:13:37,720
- Irving just:::
